CERCOPITHECINE HERPESVIRUS 1, ROCK-MONKEYS - TAIWAN (02)
**************************************************
A ProMED-mail post
<http://www.promedmail.org>
ProMED-mail is a program of the
International Society for Infectious Diseases
<http://www.isid.org>
Date: Fri 21 Jan 2005
From: Robert Peters <microbiobob641@msn.com>

A Suggestion
------------
I would like to suggest that the officials responsible get in touch with
Dr. Julia Hilliard at Georgia State University, who is a respected world
authority on this virus, regarding the proper procedures for handling bite
situations and, perhaps diagnosing this sometimes difficult-to-detect
infection in the macaque.
--
Robert L. Peters, Ph.D.
Consultant in Animal Diagnostics
<microbiobob641@msn.com>
